rdshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","of Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, England":"Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hampton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from any of numerous places called Hampton, including the cities of Southampton and Northampton (both of which were originally simply <i>Hamtun</i>). These all share the final Old English element <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’, but the first is variously <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’, <i>hamm</i> ‘water meadow’, or <i>hēan</i>, weak dative case (originally used after a preposition and article) of <i>hēah</i> ‘high’. This surname is also found in Ireland, having first been taken there in the medieval period.","History: The descendants of the clergyman Thomas Hampton, resident at Jamestown, VA, in 1630, lived in VA through three generations, multiplying their homesteads as the colony expanded and then branched into SC. This very common English name was brought independently to North America by many other bearers."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":6,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":37,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":62,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Hampton was born on 19 October 1252, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England as the daughter of Stephen de Hampton and Mrs Stephen de Hampton. She married Walter de la Poyle about 1274, in Guildford, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1317."},"et":{"19 October 1252–after 1317":"19. oktoober 1252–pärast 1317","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1273–1318":"1273–1318","–1252":"–1252","–Female":"Surnud","1252":"1252","1273":"1273","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Abt 1274":"umbes 1274","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","after 1317":"pärast 1317","1268":"1268","19 October 1252":"19. oktoober 1252","1298":"1298","about 1249":"umbes 1249","about 1273":"umbes 1273","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","Guildford, Surrey, England":"Guildford, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Hamton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, England":"Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"19 October 1252–after 1317":"19. lokakuuta 1252–1317 jälkeen","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1273–1318":"1273–1318","–1252":"–1252","–Female":"Kuollut","1252":"1252","1273":"1273","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Abt 1274":"noin 1274","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","after 1317":"1317 jälkeen","1268":"1268","19 October 1252":"19. lokakuuta 1252","1298":"1298","about 1249":"noin 1249","about 1273":"noin 1273","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","Guildford, Surrey, England":"Guildford, Surrey, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Hamton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, England":"Hampton Poyle, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"19 October 1252–after 1317":"19 octobre 1252–après 1317","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","1250–1298":"1250–1298","1273–1318":"1273–1318","–1252":"–1252","–Female":"Décédée","1252":"1252","1273":"1273","1250":"1250","1